return_calculations = function(portfolio){
  reb_month =  unique(portfolio$date)
  reb_stock = unique(portfolio$symbol)
  temp_holder = NULL
  temp_holder2 = NULL
  pb = txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = length(reb_stock), initial = 0, style = 3)
  count = 1
    for (j in 1:length(reb_stock)){
      temp_holder = portfolio %>% filter(symbol == reb_stock[j])
      temp_holder$rets  = (((lead(temp_holder$adjusted) - temp_holder$adjusted))  / temp_holder$adjusted)
      temp_holder2 = rbind(temp_holder,temp_holder2) 
      count = count + 1
      setTxtProgressBar(pb,count)
        }
  return(temp_holder2)
}

decile_seperation = function(portfolio){
  portfolio = portfolio %>% filter(available_returns >= 8) # Above 8 monthly returns in ranking 
  portfolio$cum_return = portfolio$cum_return / portfolio$available_returns #Normalising 
  reb_month =  unique(portfolio$date) # Finding all unique dates 
  temp_holder = NULL # Empty working var
  temp_holder2 = NULL # Empty working var 
  temp_holder3 = NULL # Empty working var 
  temp_holder4 = NULL # Empty working var 
  pb = txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = length(reb_month), initial = 0, style = 3)
  count = 1
    for (j in 1:length(reb_month)){
      temp_holder = portfolio %>% filter(date == reb_month[j])
      temp_holder2 = cut(temp_holder$cum_return,
          quantile(temp_holder$cum_return,probs=seq(from=0,to=1,by=1/10),na.rm =T),
          include.lowest=TRUE, 
          labels=FALSE)
       temp_holder3 = add_column(temp_holder ,as.tibble(temp_holder2))
       nrow = nrow(temp_holder3)
              count= count +1
              setTxtProgressBar(pb,count)
       if (j == 1){ 
       temp_holder4  = temp_holder3
       }
       if (j > 1){
       temp_holder4[nrow-1] = add_row(temp_holder4, temp_holder3)
       }
    } 
  return(temp_holder4)
}  

test = as.tibble(decile_seperation(df))

decile_seperation = function(portfolio){
  portfolio = portfolio %>% filter(available_returns >= 8) # Above 8 monthly returns in ranking 
  portfolio$cum_return = portfolio$cum_return / portfolio$available_returns #Normalising 
  reb_month =  unique(portfolio$date) # Finding all unique dates 
  temp_holder = NULL # Empty working var
  temp_holder2 = NULL # Empty working var 
  temp_holder3 = NULL # Empty working var 
  temp_holder4 = NULL # Empty working var 
  pb = txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = length(reb_month), initial = 0, style = 3)
  count = 1
    for (j in 1:length(reb_month)){
      temp_holder = portfolio %>% filter(date == reb_month[j])
      temp_holder2 = cut(temp_holder$cum_return,
          quantile(temp_holder$cum_return,probs=seq(from=0,to=1,by=1/10),na.rm =T),
          include.lowest=TRUE, 
          labels=FALSE)
       temp_holder3 = add_column(temp_holder ,as.tibble(temp_holder2))
       nrow = nrow(temp_holder3)
              count= count +1
              setTxtProgressBar(pb,count)
       if (j == 1){ 
       temp_holder4  = temp_holder3
       }
       if (j > 1){
       temp_holder4[nrow-1] = add_row(temp_holder4, temp_holder3)
       }
    } 
  return(temp_holder4)
}

return_calculations = function(portfolio){
  reb_month =  unique(portfolio$date)
  v = portfolio[1:3]
  ret = as.list.data.frame(c(1:nrow(portfolio)))
  pb = txtProgressBar(min = 0, max = nrow(portfolio), initial = 0, style = 3)
  count = 1
    for (j in 1:length(reb_month)){
      dd = reb_month[j]
      portfolio = v
      portfolio = portfolio %>% filter(date == as.Date(dd))
      for (i in 1:nrow(portfolio)){
        if (nrow(portfolio) > 0){ 
            x = df %>% filter(date == portfolio$date[i])%>% filter(symbol == portfolio$symbol[i])# The specific stock to invest in. 
            z = df %>% filter(symbol == x[1,1]) %>%  filter(date > portfolio[i,2])
            m = z[1,2]   # returns the stock plus one month 
            n = df %>% filter(symbol == z[1,1]) %>% filter (date == m) # locates the return for this stock
            ret[count] = ((n$adjusted   - x$adjusted)  / x$adjusted)
            setTxtProgressBar(pb,count)
            count = count + 1
        }
        else{
           print(" NA for monthly return ")
        }
      }
     
    }
   return(ret)
   
}

top$port_ret = (return_calculations(top))
bot$port_ret = (return_calculations(bot))

cumalative_ret_portfolio = function (portfolio){ 
reb_month =  unique(portfolio$date)
tot_ret = c()
  for (i in 1:length(reb_month)){
    if (i == 1){ 
    z = portfolio %>% filter(reb_month[i] == portfolio$date) # Select the first date on the list 
    ret = (1+z$port_ret) * (1/nrow(z))  # Investing 1 dollar devided by stocks multiplied with returns
    tot_ret[i]  = sum(ret) # Summerize all the returns from investing one dollar 
    }
    if (i > 1){ 
    z = portfolio %>% filter(reb_month[i] == portfolio$date)
    temp = tot_ret / nrow(z)
    ret = (1+z$port_ret) * temp
    tot_ret[i]  = sum(ret)
    }
  }
return(tot_ret)
}

total_port_ret = function (portfolio){
  portfolio = portfolio %>% filter(port_ret != 0)
  tot_ret = (cumalative_ret_portfolio(portfolio))
  return(tot_ret)
}
